Jeanette Chabalala, News24(Karabo Mokoena, Twitter) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; A memorial service to honour Karabo Mokoena, who was allegedly killed by her ex-boyfriend, will be held on Wednesday.The service will take place at the Diepkloof hall in Soweto at 14:00.Mokoena's burnt body was found in a veld in Lyndhurst, Johannesburg, on April 29. She was reported missing the day before.&nbsp;Sandile Kagiso Mantsoe, 27, was charged with killing the 22-year-old part-time student and defeating the ends of justice.He is expected back in the Johannesburg Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on May 24 for a formal bail application. &nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.